    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>To diagnose COVID-19 patients in the field, a sensitive point-of-care test using saliva was developed. Using a heat block without centrifuge, the test took 45 minutes. Naked eye judgement with color change dye outperformed the reference standard, with a diagnostic sensitivity of 82.6% (19/23) and diagnostic specificity of 100% (21/21).</jats:p>",
